Skills and Abilities. Batman has no inherent superpowers. He relies on his own scientific

knowledge, detective skills, and athletic prowess. In the stories, Batman is regarded

3

4
00:00:18,959 --> 00:00:23,680
Batman has been repeatedly described as having genius-level intellect, one of the greatest

5
00:00:23,680 --> 00:00:30,600
martial artists in the DC universe, and having peak human physical conditioning. He has traveled

6
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:35,720
the world acquiring the skills needed to aid his crusade against crime.

7
00:00:35,720 --> 00:00:40,959
His knowledge and expertise in almost every discipline known to man is nearly unparalleled

8
00:00:40,959 --> 00:00:47,480
by any other character in the universe. Batman's inexhaustible wealth allows him to access

9
00:00:47,480 --> 00:00:53,680
advanced technology. As a proficient scientist, he is able to use and modify those technologies

10
00:00:53,680 --> 00:01:00,680
to his advantage. Batman describes Superman as the most dangerous man on earth, able to

11
00:01:01,439 --> 00:01:08,279
defeat a team of super-powered extraterrestrials by himself in order to rescue his imprisoned

12
00:01:08,279 --> 00:01:15,279
teammates in the first storyline. Superman also considers Batman to be one of the most

13
00:01:15,839 --> 00:01:21,480
brilliant minds on the planet. Batman has the ability to function under great

14
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:28,480
physical pain and withstand mind control. He is a master of disguise, multilingual,

15
00:01:28,959 --> 00:01:35,959
and an expert in espionage, often gathering information under different identities. Batman's

16
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:44,440

17
00:01:45,279 --> 00:01:53,120
